<paragraph blockId="19.[176,1235,1749,1840]" lastBlockId="20.[166,1225,1153,1436]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="215" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1934" box="[398,550,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Prohypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis box="[398,416,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[428,550,1750,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[693,813,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[693,711,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[724,813,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[868,976,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[868,886,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[899,976,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the group of species represented by reddish-yellow, large flies with elongated pedicel and flagellomere 1 (latter parallel-sided, twice as long as wide and apically blunt), lacking outer vertical setae, moderately long body, setose mid and hind coxae, short preapical ventral setae on mid and hind femur, short setulose scutellum with 4 scutellar setae, easily differing from all known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[965,1110,1185,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[965,1110,1185,1211]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by almost entirely dark brown wing (
<figureCitation box="[458,528,1217,1244]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[165,198,1041,1063]" captionTargetBox="[336,1043,174,1018]" captionTargetId="figure-351@20.[336,1043,174,1042]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 22. Campylocera nigripennis: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 —head, left; 3 — head, anterior view; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — fore and mid coxae; 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior; 7 — mid coxa, femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — hind coxae; 9 — abdomen, ventrolateral view; 10 —wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453751/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">fig. 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[537,564,1217,1243]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[166,199,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[255,1063,1151,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-429@10.[246,1073,1138,1759]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 10. Campylocera latigenis: holotype Ơ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, right; 4 — head, dorsal view; 5 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453716/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis box="[537,564,1217,1243]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), winding vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[751,776,1236,1250]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">2+3</subScript>
, facial carina wide and low, ocellar, postocellar, anterior notopleural and katepisternal setae lacking. Wing length 9.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453751" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453751/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" startId="20.[165,198,1041,1063]" targetBox="[336,1043,174,1018]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[165,1225,1039,1116]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
Fig. 22. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[240,477,1041,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis box="[240,477,1041,1063]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 
<emphasis box="[708,719,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">1</emphasis>
— habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis box="[954,965,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">2</emphasis>
—head, left; 
<emphasis box="[1091,1102,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">3</emphasis>
— head, anterior view; 
<emphasis box="[279,290,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">4</emphasis>
— mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis box="[567,578,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">5</emphasis>
— fore and mid coxae; 
<emphasis box="[802,813,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">6</emphasis>
— fore femur and tibia, posterior; 
<emphasis box="[1143,1154,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">7</emphasis>
— mid coxa, femur and tibia, anterior; 
<emphasis box="[470,481,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">8</emphasis>
— hind coxae; 
<emphasis box="[630,641,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">9</emphasis>
— abdomen, ventrolateral view; 
<emphasis box="[959,982,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">10</emphasis>
—wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="20.[166,1225,1153,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
R e m a r k. Known from a unique male only, this species is believed to belong in the group of species, which includes 
<taxonomicName box="[560,653,1313,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewi">
<emphasis box="[560,579,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[593,653,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">loewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[668,796,1313,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[668,687,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[702,796,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related species, differing by the numerous autapomorphic characters (low facial carina, ocellar and anterior notopleural setae lacking, wing dark brown). Otherwise it fits the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[904,1056,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[904,1056,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its essential characters, and I synonymize 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1942" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[516,899,1409,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Lygiohypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[516,708,1409,1435]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Lygiohypotyphla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Enderlein, G." box="[714,899,1409,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" pagination="98 - 134" refId="ref11407" refString="Enderlein, G. 1942. Klassifikation der Pyrgotiden. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschenden Freunde zu Berlin, (1941) (2), 98 - 134." type="journal article" year="1942">Enderlein, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[906,947,1409,1435]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[960,977,1409,1435]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">n</emphasis>
. with it.
</paragraph>
